<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="70" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="70">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="70">
This is a very rare species only known from China, Myanmar and Vietnam. It is close to 
<taxonomicName genus="Aphordisium" lsidName="Aphordisium cribricolle" pageId="3" pageNumber="70" rank="species" species="cribricolle">Aphordisium cribricolle</taxonomicName>
Poll, 1890, but can be separated by the morphological feature of pronotum and the typical color of the legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="70" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="70">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="70">
